<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fla. St. Player Charged in Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- A Florida State backup defensive tackle  
was arrested on attempted murder charges Friday in connection with 
a drive-by shooting. 
</P>
<P>
	Bryne Malone, 22, was charged with six counts of attempted  
first-degree murder and possession of a firearm during the 
commission of a felony, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	As a result of his arrest, assistant coach Chuck Amato said  
Malone was kicked off the team. ``We're upset,'' Amato said. 
</P>
<P>
	Julian Moore, 20, also was charged with four counts of attempted  
first-degree murder and possession of a firearm during the 
commission of a felony. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses told police that Malone and Moore drove up to a house  
Friday afternoon and fired several shots at the residence. 
</P>
<P>
	Two people were standing in the front doorway and two others  
were inside the home, but none were injured, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Malone and Moore were spotted and detained by Florida State  
University police. 
</P>
<P>
	Police found more than a dozen .22-caliber bullets in Malone's  
pocket and two bullets inside the house. They found a firearm 
inside the car. 
</P>
<P>
	A third suspect was detained but later released, police said.  
</P>
<P>
	Malone, a 6-foot-7, 263-pound sophomore from Frisco City, Ala.,  
played in nine games last season, with 14 tackles and a sack. 
</P>
</TEXT>
