<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 40; Nasdaq Is Up 43 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened higher. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is up 40 points in today's early going. 
Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 2-1 lead over 
decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 43 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up more than seven points. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street wraps up an impressive month today.  
</P>
<P>
	With just one trading session left, the Dow has already posted  
one of its best monthly percentage gains of the century. 
</P>
<P>
	The blue-chip index is up nearly 1,100 points in April, a month  
typically seen as less than stellar. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow currently has a three-day streak of gains, and not  
surprisingly, three record closes in a row. 
</P>
<P>
	And after three straight declines, the Nasdaq composite is  
showing early life as some bargain-hunters move into the high-tech 
sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
