<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boeing May Increase Ellipso Stake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Boeing Co. is exploring the possibility of  
significantly increasing its stake in Ellipso, a global satellite 
venture that would deliver telephone, e-mail and fax services, an 
official close to the discussions said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Boeing now has about a 10 percent stake, worth $50 million, in  
Mobile Communications Holdings Inc., a privately held company that 
is overseeing the Ellipso satellite venture. The official, who 
spoke on condition of anonymity, said Boeing may take a stake 
anywhere from 65 to 85 percent, valued at $400 million to $600 
million. 
</P>
<P>
	A spokeswoman for Boeing Co. said the company's talks with  
Ellipso are ``exploratory'' and that it is talking to other global 
satellite ventures as well. She would not comment on the nature of 
Boeing's discussions with Ellipso. 
</P>
<P>
	Ellipso plans to launch the satellites in late 2001 and be in  
service by 2002. Ellipso wouldn't offer service directly to 
consumers and businesses but would lease its transmission 
facilities to other companies, which would provide services to 
customers. 
</P>
<P>
	Boeing has a contract with Ellipso to be its main systems  
integrator, the company spokeswoman said. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
