<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NCAA Penalizes Cal State Fullerton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FULLERTON, Calif. (AP) -- The NCAA placed Cal State Fullerton on  
four years of probation today for violations involving the men's 
basketball program. 
</P>
<P>
	The Division I infraction's committee also restricted the  
university from awarding grants-in-aid to junior college transfer 
student-athletes for three years. 
</P>
<P>
	The violations mostly involved recruiting of prospective  
student-athletes and providing prospects with improper inducements. 
</P>
<P>
	``The committee also found a lack of institutional control and  
that the university failed to adequately monitor its athletics 
programs,'' the NCAA said in a statement from Overland Park, Kan. 
</P>
<P>
	The committee said that during summer and fall 1993 and summer  
1994, several prospective men's basketball players enrolled in 
junior colleges received assistance with registering and paying the 
costs of correspondence courses at other institutions. 
</P>
<P>
	The prospects also received assistance in course registration at  
junior colleges and payment of tuition costs, and received improper 
cash payments, lodging, transportation and other benefits, the NCAA 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
