<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 11:10 a.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Japan's Jobless Rate Hits Record  
</P>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Corporate restructuring efforts helped send Japan's  
jobless rate to yet another record high of 4.8 percent last month. 
The latest government unemployment rate figure reported today 
topped the previous all-time high of 4.6 percent set in February. 
Jobs remain scarce and the situation is unlikely to improve soon, 
government officials say. The jobless data are likely to heighten 
pessimism about the nation's economy, which could further hurt 
chances for a turnaround as worried consumers curtail spending. 
Lackluster consumer spending is a major reason the Japanese economy 
has not been able to rescue itself. 

</P>
<P>
	Economy Grows at 4.5 Percent Rate  
</P>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The remarkable U.S. economy grew at a strong  
4.5 percent annual rate in the first three months of this year, far 
above expectations, as consumers spent at the fastest pace in more 
than a decade. The Commerce Department reported that the solid 
growth in the gross domestic product, the total output of goods and 
services, came despite the fact that the nation's trade deficit, 
battered by overseas economic turmoil, soared to a record level 
from January through March, subtracting 2.4 percentage points from 
overall growth. Without this drag from trade, which amounted to a 
loss of $55.6 billion in output, the GDP would grow at an even more 
remarkable 6.9 percent in the first quarter. 

</P>
<P>
	Stocks Higher in Early Trading  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks moved higher in early trading today,  
gaining strength from a government report that said the U.S. 
economy grew faster than expected in the first quarter. Just before 
11 a.m. EDT, the Dow Jones industrial average was up 40.95 to 
10,919.33. The Dow has set a record high close in each of the last 
three sessions. Leading the Dow higher was Minnesota Mining and 
Manufacturing, up 4 1/16 to 89 11/16, which reported higher than 
expected first-quarter profits. Broader stock indicators also rose. 
The Nasdaq composite index was up 38.94 to 2,567.38. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures just before 11 a.m. EDT:  
Dow Industrials:        10919.33  + 40.95
