<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bucks' Robinson Injures Knee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Glenn Robinson, the Milwaukee Bucks' leading  
scorer, strained a ligament in his right knee in the first quarter 
against Detroit tonight. Although he returned later in the quarter, 
he was scratched for the second half. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson was standing near the Detroit basket when Pistons star  
Grant Hill hit the floor and rolled onto Robinson's right leg with 
6:20 left in the quarter. He writhed in pain for about 30 seconds 
and was helped off the court and into the locker room. 
</P>
<P>
	Robinson, who averages 18.7 points, returned with 5.6 seconds  
left in the period, his right knee in a sleeve. 
</P>
<P>
	He didn't come out after halftime, nor did teammate Dell Curry,  
who was limited to four minutes in the first half because of back 
spasms. 
</P>
<P>
	The teams began the night tied for the sixth spot in the Eastern  
Conference playoff race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
