<HEADLINE> Mom Sentenced for Suffocating Baby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANFORD, Fla. (AP) -- A woman who suffocated her newborn son in a  
plastic bag was sentenced to 21 years in prison after pleading no 
contest to second-degree murder. 
</P>
<P>
	The sentence, handed down Thursday to Jannifer Butler, 27,  
includes no possibility of parole. Prosecutors sought to keep Ms. 
Butler jailed until after her childbearing years, Assistant State 
Attorney Gino Feliciani said. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said Ms. Butler had zipped her newborn baby into a  
plastic comforter bag and hid him in a closet after giving birth on 
Christmas Day 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	They said she concealed her pregnancy before and after giving  
birth because she said her family was having money problems. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors had sought the death penalty for Ms. Butler after  
she pleaded innocent by reason of insanity to first-degree murder. 
Her no-contest plea to a lesser charge averted a trial scheduled 
for next week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
