<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dollar Rises Against Yen and Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The dollar rose against the Japanese yen and the  
euro today as another round of positive U.S. economic data 
overwhelmed the foreign exchange market. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro, the common currency of 11 European nations, fell to  
yet another low as the data were released. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's more of a U.S. story,'' even overtaking the continued  
conflict in Kosovo that has undermined the euro, said Jay Bryson, 
an international economist at First Union Capital Markets in 
Charlotte, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
	In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 119.40  
Japanese yen, up from 119.03 yen late Thursday. The euro fell 
against the dollar, trading at $1.0582, down from $1.0591. During 
the trading day, the euro fell to $1.0550, its lowest point since 
its January launch. 
</P>
<P>
	Traders liked U.S. economic data released Friday and used it to  
push the dollar higher. 
</P>
<P>
	The Commerce Department reported that the gross domestic product  
grew 4.5 percent in the first three months of the year, greater 
than the 3.9 percent growth for all of 1998. Inflation was a 
no-show. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro's fall was halted, however, by traders' fears caused by  
previous comments by European officials. The head of the German 
central bank, Hans Tietmeyer, made remarks Thursday indicating that 
the European Central Bank could well intervene to prop up the euro 
if necessary, Bryson said. 
</P>
<P>
	The yen was weakened Friday by fresh negative economic data,  
with Japan's jobless rate rising and wages falling. 
</P>
<P>
	The dollar was quoted at 1.5243 Swiss francs, up from 1.5202,  
and 1.4587 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4665 late Thursday. The 
British pound was quoted at $1.6090, up from $1.6088. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro no  
longer are traded separately and are tied to the euro by a fixed 
rate. Based on the euro rate, the dollar was worth: 1.8484 German 
marks, up from 1.8467; 6.1996 French francs, up from 6.1920; and 
1,828.15 Italian lire, unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
