<HEADLINE> Steelers Extend Stewart's Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Quarterback Kordell Stewart has agreed to a  
deal with the Pittsburgh Steelers that will take him at least 
through the 2003 season. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms were not available, and the team will make no official  
announcement until Stewart's agent, Leigh Steinberg, returns from 
vacation in 10 days, the Pittsburgh Post-Gazette reported today. 
</P>
<P>
	Team officials were not immediately available for comment, but  
Stewart's new contract was filed with the NFL. 
</P>
<P>
	The extension will keep Stewart with the Steelers for at least  
five more years. He had been under contract for two more seasons 
under a 1997 extension; that was his first as a starting 
quarterback for the team. 
</P>
<P>
	He was scheduled to earn $2.05 million next season and $2.5  
million in 2000. 
</P>
