<HEADLINE> Stephen Got Even Is Derby Favorite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Lightly raced Stephen Got Even, 12-1 on  
the morning line, was the lukewarm 4-1 favorite for the Kentucky 
Derby after early wagering today at Churchill Downs. 
</P>
<P>
	Maybe it is Steven Got Even's three-race winning streak,  
including a Grade II stakes race at Turfway Park on March 27, or 
perhaps his connections, trainer Nick Zito and jockey Chris 
McCarron. Zito won the 1991 Derby with Strike the Gold and the 1994 
Derby with Go for Gin; McCarron rode Go for Gin and won the 1987 
Derby aboard Alysheba. 
</P>
<P>
	Blue Grass Stakes winner Menifee and Florida Derby winner Vicar  
are each 5-1. Menifee was 5-1 and Vicar was 6-1 on the morning 
line. 
</P>
<P>
	After the early wagering, the Bob Baffert entry of Excellent  
Meeting and General Challenge is 6-1. The entry was the 3-1 
favorite when wagering opened. The Baffert-trained Prime Timber, 
second choice on the morning line at 7-2, is 12-1. 
</P>
<P>
	Many in Friday's crowd went for the mutuel field, which includes  
Risen Star winner Ecton Park, Arkansas Derby winner Valhol, 
Louisiana Derby winner Kimberlite Pipe, Lemon Drop Kid and K One 
King. The field is 7-1, down from 12-1 on the morning line. 
</P>
<P>
	Other morning line odds and odds after the early wagering:  
</P>
<P>
	Worldly Manner, 12-1, 15-1.  
</P>
<P>
	Adonis, 30-1, 20-1.  
</P>
<P>
	Three Ring, 20-1, 20-1.  
</P>
<P>
	Desert Hero, 15-1, 19-1.  
</P>
<P>
	Answer Lively, 50-1, 25-1.  
</P>
<P>
	Cat Thief, 8-1, 7-1.  
</P>
<P>
	First American, 50-1, 40-1.  
</P>
<P>
	Charismatic, 20-1, 30-1.  
</P>
