<HEADLINE> Former Piston Caught in Drug House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Former Detroit Piston Earl Cureton was caught in  
a suspected drug house yesterday and was charged with a misdemeanor 
of loitering in a place of illegal occupation, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Four others were also charged in the raid on a Detroit home,  
including two with a felony of intent to deliver. 
</P>
<P>
	``His demeanor to me was that he's embarrassed to be caught up  
in this,'' Sgt. Marlene Sanders of the police narcotics section 
said. ``He said it was just bad luck.'' 
</P>
<P>
