<DOCNO> APW19990430.0212 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-30 09:05:08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dole Wants Bigger Free Trade Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Elizabeth Dole is calling for an extended free  
trade zone that includes Central and South America and for bringing 
China into the World Trade Organization. 
</P>
<P>
	The Clinton administration has failed to put its muscle behind  
free trade since the North American Free Trade Agreement was 
adopted five years ago, Mrs. Dole, who is weighing a bid for 
president, told an Economic Club of Detroit luncheon Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Frankly, since the bipartisan success of NAFTA, the great  
sucking sound we hear is the administration's international 
leadership vacuum,'' Mrs. Dole said. 
</P>
<P>
	But Gore press secretary Chris Lehane said the administration  
has a strong record on free trade: ``What you're really hearing is 
the sucking sound of a sputtering campaign.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Dole also called on Congress to give President Clinton  
fast-track authority to negotiate trade deals. That authority would 
provide for a rapid review of trade agreements by Congress. 
</P>
<P>
	``Every president from Gerald Ford to George Bush has had  
fast-track authority,'' she said. She said Congress should give it 
to Clinton ``and to his successor, whoever she may be,'' drawing 
whoops and applause with her gender reference. 
</P>
<P>
	She also called for a Western Hemisphere free trade zone, saying  
the inclusion of Central and South America would promote stability 
and freedom. NAFTA covers the United States, Mexico and Canada. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's also time, under the tough conditions just negotiated,  
that the United States move forward toward the entry of China into 
the World Trade Organization,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Calling Serbian leader Slobodan Milosevic ``evil personified,''  
Mrs. Dole said she backs stepped-up air attacks on Yugoslavia and 
the stationing of ground troops nearby for possible future use. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
