<HEADLINE> Oil Prices Extend Gains Oil Prices  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Prices of contracts for future delivery of crude  
oil rose today on the New York Mercantile Exchange, extending a 
rally that has lifted oil prices to 16-month highs. 
</P>
<P>
	But some petroleum product contracts fell in commodity trading  
as traders took profits on recent sharp gains. 
</P>
<P>
	The rally in crude oil has been helped by declining supplies,  
reflecting production cutbacks promised by the Organization of the 
Petroleum Exporting Countries in an attempt to bolster prices. 
</P>
<P>
	Light, sweet crude oil for delivery in June rose 13 cents to  
close at $18.66 a barrel on the Nymex. 
</P>
<P>
	In London, North Sea Brent Blend crude oil for delivery in June  
rose 12 cents to $16.57 a barrel. 
</P>
<P>
	Profit-taking sent petroleum products falling on the Nymex.  
</P>
<P>
	May contracts for heating oil fell 0.32 cent to 44.47 cents a  
gallon, May unleaded gasoline slipped 0.75 cent to 54.47 cents a 
gallon and June natural gas fell 8.6 cents to $2.253 for each 1,000 
cubic feet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
