<HEADLINE> UTC Names New President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- United Technologies Corp. has named Karl  
Krapek, who has been president of its Pratt &AMP; Whitney jet-engine 
division, as president and chief operating officer of the parent 
company. 
</P>
<P>
	Krapek, 50, was elected Friday to take over responsibilities  
that UTC chairman and chief executive George David had been 
handling. David continues in the company's two top posts, 
</P>
<P>
	Replacing Krapek as president of Pratt &AMP; Whitney is Louis  
Chenevert, 41, formerly an executive vice president of operations 
at Pratt. 
</P>
<P>
	The UTC board also approved a two-for-one stock split, and  
declared a quarterly cash dividend of 36 cents on the pre-split 
common shares. 
</P>
<P>
	This is the company's first stock split in the form of a  
dividend since December 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Both the stock dividend and the cash dividend will be payable to  
shareholders on May 7. The stock dividend will be issued May 17, 
while the cash dividend will be paid June 10. 

</P>
</TEXT>
